[src:line-segment-intersection/line-line-intersection] There will be an intersection if 0 ≤ *t* ≤ 1 and 0 ≤ *u* ≤ 1.
[src:line-segment-intersection/line-line-intersection] The intersection point falls within the first line segment if 0 ≤ *t* ≤ 1, and it falls within the second line segment if 0 ≤ *u* ≤ 1.
[src:line-segment-intersection/line-line-intersection] These inequalities can be tested without the need for division, allowing rapid determination of the existence of any line segment intersection before calculating its exact point.
